column4: <content>Problem of Bruegel imitators: J. Savery (see the many landscape drawings attr. to him by Münz) but also M. 38 Bruegel sons (after which J. de Gheyn made an etching. Imitators of Naer het Leven drawings R. Savery, Quast (Album Amicorum v. Gelder) Saftleven (mentioned by van Leeuwen in Simiolus, see edinburgh)[...]</content>

<parts.title>[2 bladen] Jacob Savery (Dyce Bequest 513) Village Festival, watercolour, signed bottom centre, in gold [...]; [blad 2, verso] R. Savery (Dyce Bequest 512) Study of Rock [...]</parts.title>

<parts.title>Bruegel motifs in Savery. [?] Flower picture: I cannot agree with Count Seilern who suggests in his catalogue IV Addenda 1969 that his N° 318 verso (pl. XXXII), (M107) is the source for the man seen from the back right of centre in the Flower picture, but I modify my statement in Boymans Bulletin V/21 July 1954, p. 50 by saying that another possibility is that the figure in the Flower painting maybe based on a lost 'Naer het Leven' drawing.</parts.title>
<object.title>Naer het Leven: Handwriting; Watermarks; Separation of hand; Photographs of Savery drawings (Albertina & Courtauld Galleries)</object.title>
